{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"f101ae88-41a1-49f8-a0d5-2fd013b49986","content":"**No, `net6.0` is not supported by MSTest v4.** \n\nMSTest 4.x dropped support for .NET 6.0 (which is already end-of-life). The minimum supported target framework is **`net8.0`** (for modern .NET).\n\nTo migrate, you'll need to update your target framework. For example:\n\n```xml\n<TargetFramework>net8.0</TargetFramework>\n```\n\nWould you like me to update your project to target `net8.0` and upgrade to MSTest v4?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"51ccbcdf-f0d4-4815-8177-09f3ae83d466","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user wants to migrate from MSTest 3.8.0 to MSTest v4 and wants to know if net6.0 is still supported.\n\nMSTest v4 dropped support for older target frameworks. MSTest 4.x requires at least .NET 8.0 (for .NET Core/5+). It dropped support for net6.0 and net7.0 as those are out of support.\n\nLet me verify this by checking the MSTest documentation or NuGet page.","outputTokens":262,"requestId":"5C2D:3C05D0:49465F:5BB3C9:69F56455"},"id":"22adeac5-fc26-433e-a513-4ae64eacb389","timestamp":"2026-05-02T02:41:32.642Z","parentId":"2bb21ae5-83e9-4a50-af04-a67fd2115a0d"}
